The '''Edith-Russ-Haus für Medienkunst''' ("Edith Russ House") is an [[art gallery]] in the city of [[Oldenburg]], [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]], dedicated to [[new media art]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.oldenburg.de/startseite/kultur/museen-kunsthaeuser/edith-russ-haus.html | title=Edith-Russ-Haus für Medienkunst | website=[http://www.oldenburg.de/ Stadt Oldenburg] | location=Germany | language=German | accessdate=13 September 2015 }}</ref>
The gallery was founded due to an endowment from [[Edith Russ]], a secondary school teacher in Oldenburg. It does not have a permanent collection but presents temporary exhibitions and associated events. The building is close to the [[Peter-Friedrich-Ludwig-Hospital]], a cultural centre and former hospital, located to the southwest.
